org.vu.contest

Interface ContestEvaluation


  • public interface ContestEvaluation

    The interface that an evaluation class must implement. This interface imposes a generic structure for an evaluation class whose purpose is to allow a submitted algorithm to evaluate results and the contest run system to get the corresponding performance metrics. The semantics of the methods' return values and arguments depend on the specific implementation of the interface.

    Evaluation objects are instantiated by the contest main run loop and passed to algorithm objects of class ContestSubmission. Calling methods getProperties, getData and evaluate allow a player's algorithm to get information about the evaluation, to receive data and to evaluate its performance.

    Method evaluate is to be used by the player's algorithm to guide its progress and register its performance with the contest system, while method getFinalResult is used by the contest run system to get an overall performance metric of the algorithm's run. An evaluation class should keep track of the performance results it returns through the evaluate method and return an appropriate final result (best, average, etc) when method getFinalResult is called by the contest run system.

    • Method Detail

      • evaluate

        java.lang.Object evaluate(java.lang.Object result)
        Evaluates a result of the algorithm and returns its performance. This method must always have a meaningful implementation. The exact meaning of "result" and "performance" depend on the type of contest and the implementation of class implementing the interface.
        Parameters:
        result - The algorithm result to be evaluated. Depending on the implementation, the semantics of the argument will differ and a specific subclass may be expected.
        Returns:
        An object denoting the performance of the result or null. Depending on the implementation, the semantics of the return value will differ and a specific subclass may be returned.

      • getData

        java.lang.Object getData(java.lang.Object key)
        Returns data relevant to the evaluation problem. This method can be used by evaluation classes implementing problems that need to pass data to the solving algorithm. A key argument can be used to address specific data. Depending on the implementation the key may be used or not and the return value may vary between calls of the method or not. The exact meaning of "data" and "key" depend on the type of contest and the implementation of class implementing the interface.
        Parameters:
        key - An object specifying what exactly data to be returned. Depending on the implementation, the semantics of the argument will differ and a specific subclass may be expected.
        Returns:
        An object representing relevant data or null. Depending on the implementation, the semantics of the return value will differ and a specific subclass may be returned.

      • getFinalResult

        double getFinalResult()
        Returns the overall performance of the algorithm run. This method is called by the contest run system after a player's algorithm has finished its run. The returned value must correspond (or summarize) to the values returned by the evaluate method during the object's lifetime.
        Returns:
        A double determining the overall performance of the algorithm for this run.

      • getProperties

        java.util.Properties getProperties()
        Returns the properties of the evaluation class. The keys contained in the properties depend on the specific implementation.
        Returns:
        A Properties object or null, depending on the implementation.
